The A2A protocol enables AI agents to communicate by defining a standardized set of messages and endpoints. For example, an AI agent could discover another agent's capabilities via an HTTP POST request to `/discover`, then securely exchange information through a `/tasks` endpoint. Here’s a simplified code snippet demonstrating an A2A agent interaction:
python
import requests

# Discover agent capabilities
response = requests.post(
    "https://agent1.example.com/discover",
    json={"capabilities": ["data_analysis", "summarization"]}
)
capabilities = response.json()

# Request collaboration on a task
if "data_analysis" in capabilities:
    task_response = requests.post(
        "https://agent2.example.com/tasks",
        json={
            "task": "analyze_dataset",
            "input": {"dataset": "sales_data.csv"}
        }
    )
    result = task_response.json()
